post_text:
SEPTEMBER SATURDAYS VIRTUAL CELEBRATION

The Communications and Community Relations Department has decided to produce four virtual September Saturdays show celebrations instead of celebrating in our traditional way on the courthouse grounds to mitigate the spread of COVID-19. Starting on September 5th, these celebrations will air each Saturday in the month of September at 7 p.m. on Dctv23. Each show will have a specific theme and consist of multiple interviews, music performances, and special guests. More details to come! We hope you'll join us on Comcast Channel 23, AT&T U-verse Channel 99, Dctv23 Facebook Page, Douglas County Happenings Facebook Page, and Dctv23 YouTube Channel. For further information, contact Rick Martin at rickmartin@co.douglas.ga.us.

WEATHER ADVISORY FOR MONDAY, AUGUST 10TH

Overview (what / where / when?) --

The threat for strong to severe storms exists across much of north & central Georgia mainly between ~2:00 PM and ~11:00 PM
Storms may be isolated to scattered initially (early to mid afternoon) but could form into larger lines/clusters later today into early this evening Primary threats:
Damaging winds > 60 MPH --> resulting in downed trees/powerlines along with some minor structural damage possible
Very heavy rain which could lead to localized flooding/flash flooding
Frequent lightning
Hail up to 1" (isolated)

post_text:
Connect Douglas will be holding a public meeting on Thursday, July 9th at 10 a.m. at the Douglas County Transportation Center at 8800 Dorris Road, Douglasville, GA 30134. Direct access to the Transportation Center is available on the Connect Douglas Fixed Routes 20 & 40.

At this meeting, Connect Douglas will explain the methodology used to establish this goal, and provide a list of proposed projects that could include DBE participation during this three-year period. The DBE Program/Policy was adopted by the Douglas County Board of Commissioners in 1999 to ensure that DBEs as defined have an equal opportunity to receive and participate in DOT-assisted contracts. In addition to the public meeting, Connect Douglas will accept comments on the DBE goal through e-mail or letter. The mailing address is Connect Douglas, 8800 Dorris Road, Douglasville, GA 30134.

Contact Connect Douglas at connectdouglas@co.douglas.ga.us

Thank you Q&8 Podcast Douglas County Sheriff's Office (Georgia) City of Douglasville - Government Douglasville Police Department Douglas County Fire/EMS Department Douglas County E-911
shared_text:
WWW.QAND8PODCAST.COM
Q&8 Podcast Episode 26 - Special Edition: Discussion with the Sheriff Tim Pounds and the Douglas County Sheriff's Office.

Q&8 Podcast
June 7 at 3:50 PM ·

With the climate of the world today and people on edge, Q & 8 decided to reach out to the community for questions they had for the local law enforcement, the Douglas County Sheriff’s Office with Sheriff Tim Pounds and his team.

The Douglas County Sheriff’s office was created in 1871 and is a leader in law enforcement with their specialized Scorpion Unit, Civil and Special Investigations Unit, Patrol Division, K9 Unit, SERT Team and much more. Sheriff Pounds also created the Community Outreach Program and Education Division, better known as S.C.O.P.E.

The main mission of S.C.O.P.E. is to bridge better relationships between the Sheriff’s Office and the community by providing resources, outreach programs and education, not only to the employees of the Douglas County Sheriff’s Office, but also the Douglas County community.

post_text:
Friday, June 5, 2020: Hazmat Spill Update:

As of 10:15 a.m. clean up efforts continue to impact the flow of traffic in Douglas County on Highway 92 and Highway 166 where a tractor-trailer overturned and caused a hazardous material situation. We're told traffic should re-open some time this morning.

DOUGLAS COUNTY ADVANCE POLLING SITE EXPERIENCES DELAYED OPENING

Douglasville, Georgia - The Douglas County Elections and Voter Registration Department wants to inform you that the Advance Polling site at Boundary Waters Aquatic Center is experiencing a delayed opening this morning due to road closures from the current hazmat spill clean-up efforts. Currently Boundary Waters Park can be accessed from the HWY 92 side (New Manchester High School Side) but not from the 166 and Fulton County side. The Advance Poling Site at the Boundary Waters Aquatic Center plans to be opened at 10:30 a.m.

post_text:
LIBERTY ROAD BRIDGE CLOSURE
GDOT will be closing the Liberty Road bridge over I-20 beginning June 1st to do improvements to the bridge. The bridge work will be similar to the work GDOT performed at Post Road and several other locations along I-20. GDOT anticipates the bridge will be closed for 45 days.

The detour route will be as follows:

Vehicles on Liberty Road headed north to points north of I-20, will be directed to take I-20 east to Post Road, turn left on Post Road, cross over the bridge there and take I-20 west back to the Liberty Road/Mirror Lake Blvd interchange. They can then exit at the westbound ramp at that interchange and turn right to continue northbound on Mirror Lake Blvd.

Similarly, vehicles traveling southbound on Liberty Road to areas south of I-20 will be directed to take I-20 west to SR 61, take the westbound exit ramp, turn left on SR 61 and cross over the bridge at that location, then take I-20 east back to Liberty Road and exit at the Liberty Road interchange then turn right to proceed southbound on Liberty Road.

Power Outage:

Crews from GreyStone Power are working to restore outages throughout an area in Lithia Springs served by the Groovers Lake substation. Shortly before 1:30 a.m. multiple sounds of explosions could be heard coming from the area of the substation. Douglas County E-911 are fielding numerous phone calls and want to assure you power crews are working to get everyone back on as quickly as possible.

If you experience an outage, please visit greystonepower.com. You can also report an outage by calling 866-GREYSTONE (473-9786) or via the GreyStone Outage Helper app.

June 2, 2020 at 6:00 p.m.

Due to the current closure of the Douglas County Courthouse, the meeting will be held online via Microsoft Teams. Public comment will be accepted on any of the applications. Douglas County Planning and Zoning

8700 Hospital Drive

Douglasville GA 30134 jwomack@co.douglas.ga.us

770-920-7260

The meeting will be livestreamed through Douglas County DCTV23, and can be accessed via the Douglas County website, Douglas County Facebook Happenings, or your local cable channel.

DOUGLAS COUNTY LANDFILL RECYCLING SERVICES TEMPORARILY SUSPENDED DUE TO COVID-19

Due to the COVID-19 epidemic, recycling of glass, plastic, and mixed paper has been temporarily suspended at the Douglas County Landfill. Douglas County Citizens who are able to temporarily store recyclables are encouraged to do so. Recycling operations will resume as soon as possible. For more information, please send emails to solidwaste@co.douglas.ga.us.
